SIMPLE: polyconic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Polyconic
<hw>Pol`y*con"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets>
+ <ets>conic</ets>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to, or based upon, many
cones.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Polyconic projection</b></col> <fld>(Map Making)</fld>,
<cd>a projection of the earth's surface, or any portion thereof, by
which each narrow zone is projected upon a conical surface that touches
the sphere along this zone, the conical surface being then unrolled.
This projection differs from <xex>conic projection</xex> in that latter
assumes but one cone for the whole map. Polyconic projection is that in
use in the United States coast and geodetic survey.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>polycosmic</ent>⟦br⟧
